    Class and Description
    Activities
    A set of multiple Activity elements, to be executed either in sequence or in parallel.
    Activity
    Abstract type used by all different types of process elements.
    Decision
    A Decision consists of a Task and a set of alternative Activity elements.
    Exit
    This activity will simply cause the workflow to exit, regardless of its current execution state.
    Loop
    A Loop contains an Activity and a Task.
    Option
    One of the alternative paths contained within a Decision
    Process
    The main business process, which must contain exactly one root Activity element.
    Script
    This activity executes a script.
    ServiceTask
    A REST service call.
    Signal
    This activity waits for an external signal trigger.
    SubProcess
    An Activity that represents the execution of an independent workflow defined elsewhere.
    Task
    A basic workflow task.
    Variable
    Variables are used to define inputs and outputs associated with a workflow or workflow activity.
    Variables
    Java class for Variables complex type.
